&lt;p&gt;The Vox Media Podcast Network is seeking a Senior Video Producer to drive multiplatform production across a diverse and high-profile slate of podcasts. This role will serve as a key creative contributor to show teams launching new video-first shows, and support production across the existing show slate as needed.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work closely with hosts, producers, and editorial stakeholders to shape each show’s unique visual and conceptual identity, develop segments/formats, and lead a weekly edit workflow. This is a hands-on role for a highly skilled and versatile video editor and visual storyteller who has experience managing freelance contributors, coaching host talent, and delivering polished, high-performing content tailored to YouTube, TikTok, Instagram, and other platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with podcast teams across the network to develop and launch new video shows, offering both creative consultation and execution support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edit and produce longform video episodes for platforms like YouTube, ensuring strong pacing, dynamic visuals, and high production value across remote, in-studio, and hybrid formats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create platform-native shortform video content optimized for TikTok, Instagram Reels, and YouTube Shorts—translating strong podcast moments into compelling visual stories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement scalable visual elements (motion graphics, captions, lower-thirds, etc.) that align with each show’s tone and target platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and mentor freelance editors and designers, assigning work, giving creative feedback, and ensuring brand consistency and quality across deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and edit scripts as needed in collaboration with hosts/show teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with editorial, social, and audience development teams to ensure shows meet performance goals and platform best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on visual and social trends across the podcast and digital media landscape, offering insights and ideas that help shows reach their target audiences and stand out from their competitive set.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;WHAT YOU’LL BRING&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6–8+ years of experience in digital video production, with a track record of success creating editorial or creator-driven content for social and streaming platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to produce both longform and shortform video content, especially for talk-based or interview-driven formats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong editing expertise in Adobe Premiere (motion design and graphics capabilities in After Effects or similar tools a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing freelancers or vendors, and clear creative direction that ensures timely, high-quality delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent editorial instincts and scriptwriting ability, with a knack for shaping pacing, tone, and story arc, especially in host-driven formats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative, consultative working style and the ability to plug into existing teams to help elevate their visual presence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A deep understanding of video platform ecosystems (YouTube, TikTok, Reels), including what drives performance, how users engage, and what makes shows grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
